                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/662: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-25T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 25, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>178. Your 327, May 24, 10 a.m., and 328, May 24, 11 a.m. in regard to the Chinese
                    Maritime Customs. In the light of your presentation of the matter in telegrams
                    under reference, Department is satisfied to let the matter rest for the present,
                    pending further developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
